document_data.Defense and Justice:
{{see also|Axe of Mirabar}}
Mirabar was defended by the [[Axe of Mirabar]], an army of around two thousand, including humans and five hundred [[dwarves]]. There was virtually no crime, and the city utilized professional thief trackers, the "[[Shadow District]]", to monitor any potential criminals.

Making maps of the city was illegal for security purposes, because the city was concerned about intelligence getting into the hands of Mirabar's enemies, especially [[Luskan]]. An attack on a councilor or a councilor-elect was punishable by execution. This was to prevent plots to foil a candidate's election campaign.
